Start to the map of students across Oregon and participation on ORExt. 

states <- map_data("state") %>%
  rename(name = region) %>%
  select(-subregion, -group) %>%
  filter(name == "oregon")

counties <- map_data("county")
or_county <- counties %>%
  filter(region == "oregon")

or_base <- ggplot(data = states) +
  geom_polygon(aes(long, lat),
               fill = "#154937",
               color = "#55565B",
               size = 2) +
  geom_bin2d(data = d, aes(lon, lat),
             binwidth = .08) +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "plasma",
                       direction = -1) +
  coord_quickmap()

or_base
## Warning: Removed 48 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin2d).

Here is a refined map of Oregon with students participation on ORExt. Counties outlined for detail. 

or_base +
  theme_void() +
  geom_polygon(data = or_county,
               aes(long, lat,
                   group = group),
               fill = NA,
               color = "#55565B")
## Warning: Removed 48 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin2d).

Next I plan to include a title additional information. 

or_base +
  theme_void() +
  geom_polygon(data = or_county,
               aes(long, lat,
                   group = group),
               fill = NA,
               color = "#55565B") +
  labs(title = "Student Participation by School Location in Oregon",
         subtitle = "Oregon's Extended Assessment for students with significant cognitive disabilities ")
